data.name: Primeape

attacks.name: Rampage
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Primeape. Flip a coin. If tails, Primeape is now Confused (after doing damage).

data.flavorText: This Pokémon only calms down when there are no other animals or people around—which means no one has ever seen it when it's not angry.

data.name: Primeape

attacks.name: Bebop Punch
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: If approached while asleep, it may awaken and angrily give chase in a groggy state of semi-sleep.

attacks.name: Toss
attacks.text: You may discard from your hand as many Technical Machine and Pokémon Tool cards as you like. This attack does 30 damage times the number of cards you discarded.

abilities.name: Scram
abilities.text: If Brock's Primeape ever has exactly 10 HP left, shuffle it and all cards attached to it into your deck. This power stops working while Brock's Primeape is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mega Thrash
attacks.text: Brock's Primeape does 20 damage to itself. If there is a Stadium card in play, discard it.

data.name: Primeape

abilities.name: Anger Point
abilities.text: If Primeape has any damage counters on it, Primeape's attacks do 40 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Whump
attacks.text: Primeape is now Confused. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

data.flavorText: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

data.name: Primeape

attacks.name: Top Drop
attacks.text: Discard the top card from your opponent's deck. If you discarded a Pokémon, this attack does damage equal to the HP of that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Brick Break
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

data.name: Dark Primeape

abilities.name: Frenzy
abilities.text: If Dark Primeape does any damage while it's Confused (even to itself), it does 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Frenzied Attack
attacks.text: Dark Primeape is now Confused (after doing damage).

data.flavorText: Although Primeapes have always been mean, lately they seem to be becoming even more vicious and frenzied.

data.name: Primeape

attacks.name: Swagger
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spirited Throw
attacks.text: If, before doing damage, your opponent's Active Pokémon has more remaining HP than this Pokémon, this attack does 60 more damage.

data.flavorText: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.

attacks.name: Wreck
attacks.text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage. Discard that Stadium card.

attacks.name: Flames of Rage
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to Primeape. This attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage for each damage counter on Primeape.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Primeape is now Confused (after doing damage).

data.flavorText: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until its quarry is caught.
